HEADWORD: kurchi
<hw>kurchi</hw></mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <def>A
tropical Asian tree (<spn>Holarrhena antidysenterica</spn> syn.
<spn>Holarrhena pubescens</spn>) with hard white wood and bark formerly
used as a remedy for dysentery and diarrhea.</def>⟦br⟧
<syn><b>Syn. --</b> ivory tree, conessi, kurchee, <spn>Holarrhena
pubescens</spn>, <spn>Holarrhena antidysenterica</spn>.</syn>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Kurd</ent>⟦br⟧
